17 (1) 'COVID-19' means severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2),
18 and any mutation or viral fragments thereof, or any disease or condition caused by severe
19 acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS-CoV-2).
20 (1)(2) 'Nonroutine stressful or strenuous physical activity' means actions that are not
21 clerical, administrative, or nonmanual in nature.
22 (2)(3) 'Public safety officer' means a law enforcement officer, firefighter, emergency
23 medical technician, emergency management rescue specialist, state highway employee,
24 or prison guard.
25 (3)(4) 'Work related activity' means, while in the line of duty:
26 (A) Engaging in a situation involving nonroutine stressful or strenuous physical
27 activity related to law enforcement, fire suppression, rescue, hazardous material
28 response, emergency medical services, prison or jail security, disaster relief, or any
29 other emergency response; or
30 (B) Participating in a training exercise involving nonroutine stressful or strenuous
31 physical activity.
32 (b) Indemnification shall be paid under this article part as follows:
33 (1) In the case of a partial permanent disability suffered in the line of duty by a public
34 safety officer while in the line of duty, the eligible disabled person may elect to receive
35 a payment of $35,000.00 paid in equal monthly installments for five years or a lump sum
36 of such amount reduced to its present value upon the basis of interest calculated at the
37 rate of 6 percent per annum;
38 (2) In the case of a total permanent disability suffered in the line of duty by a public
39 safety officer while in the line of duty, the injured eligible disabled person may elect to
40 receive a payment of $75,000.00 paid in equal monthly installments for five years or a
41 lump sum of such amount reduced to its present value upon the basis of interest
42 calculated at the rate of 6 percent per annum;
