43 (3)(A) In the case of death suffered in the line of duty by a public safety officer while
44 in the line of duty, payment shall be made to:
45 (i) The surviving unremarried spouse;
46 (ii) The surviving children who are under the age of 19 or, if a student enrolled in an
47 institution of postsecondary education at the time of such death, under the age of 24;
48 or
49 (iii) Individuals not otherwise provided for under this subparagraph who are the
50 dependents of the spouse or deceased person as shown in the spouse's or deceased
51 person's most recent tax return.
52 (B) In the case of organic brain damage suffered in the line of duty by a public safety
53 officer while in the line of duty, payment shall be made to the legal guardian of the
54 organically brain damaged person.
55 (C) The surviving unremarried spouse, dependents, or the legal guardian who qualified
56 for indemnification payment pursuant to this paragraph may elect to receive a payment
57 in a lump sum payment of $150,000.00 paid in equal monthly installments for five
58 years or a lump sum of such amount reduced to its present value upon the basis of
59 interest calculated at the rate of 6 percent per annum; or.
60 (c)(1) After the department, or the commission upon review of a denial by the
61 department, determines that a public safety officer suffered a total permanent disability,
62 a partial permanent disability, organic brain damage, or death while in the line of duty,
63 the department shall be authorized to make the appropriate payments as provided in
64 subsection (b) of this Code section. The department shall be authorized to purchase
65 annuities to fund payments issued pursuant to this part.
