100 SECTION 2.
101 Said part is further amended by revising Code Section 45-9-86, relating to application for
102 indemnification, as follows:
103 "45-9-86.
104 (a) As used in this Code section, the term terms 'COVID-19' and 'public safety officer'
105 shall have the same meaning meanings as provided in Code Section 45-9-85.
106 (b) An application for indemnification with respect to a claim for total permanent
107 disability or partial permanent disability of a public safety officer shall be submitted by that
108 person unless the person is mentally incompetent, in which case the application may be
109 made on such person's behalf by his or her legal guardian.
110 (c) An application for indemnification with respect to a claim for the death of a public
111 safety officer shall be submitted by or on behalf of the surviving unremarried spouse or
112 dependents eligible under this part.
113 (d) Except as provided in subsection (e) of this Code section, an An application for
114 indemnification with respect to death, organic brain damage, total permanent disability, or
115 partial permanent disability must be made within 24 months after the date of the incident
116 giving rise to the death, organic brain damage, or disability.
117 (e) An application for indemnification with respect to a claim for the death of a public
118 safety officer related to COVID-19 that occurred on or before April 15, 2022, shall be
119 submitted between the effective date of this Code section and August 1, 2025. No
120 indemnification claim for the death of a public safety officer related to COVID-19 that
121 occurred on or before April 15, 2022, shall be paid for an application not properly
122 submitted between the effective date of this Code section and August 1, 2025."
