123 SECTION 3.
124 Said part is further amended by revising Code Section 45-9-88, relating to indemnification
125 not to be awarded when penal violation, suicide, intentionally self-inflicted injuries, natural
126 causes, or performance of certain routine duties caused or contributed to death or disability,
127 as follows:
128 "45-9-88.
129 (a) No indemnification shall be awarded to any person otherwise entitled thereto who
130 violates a penal law of this state which violation caused or contributed to the death or
131 disability of the officer.
132 (b) Notwithstanding any other provision of this article part, no payment shall be authorized
133 if death, organic brain damage, total permanent disability, or partial permanent disability
134 occurs from suicide, intentionally self-inflicted injuries, natural causes, or the performance
135 of routine duties which would not be considered strenuous or dangerous by a reasonable
136 person, except as provided for in subsection (b) (c) of Code Section 45-9-85."
137 SECTION 4.
138 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
